1.title: Guns and Glory
1.plot: Steven is approached by the wife of an injured military veteran to see if they can recreate a military scenario for her recently retired husband as a surprise. Despite a small power outage, it is business as usual at the range. Kenny, in the dark, purchases a single fire Savage pistol. When the power comes on, they sell a shotgun to a guy who wants to shoot unusual targets on the range and help a mom find the right gun for home protection.

2.title: Office Space Invaders
2.plot: Payton has the brilliant idea to get new customers by creating a first person video game experience at the range. Biff, while trying to find more things for the store comes across an antique box gun from the 1800's He's paid a lot, but if it fires it is going to be more than worth it. Kenny gets a great deal on a US made Russian rifle, while Steven has one shot to sell a 50 cal rifle. All while helping an IT expert get rid of some e-waste.

3.title: Agent Gunsmith
3.plot: Two customers want to live out a Matrix style fantasy, while Steven gets to live out a fantasy of combining two of his favorite things. Monster trucks and explosions. Kenny hires one of Payton's friends, and Biff gets a great price on two early edition pistols.

4.title: Shotgun Wedding
4.plot: Cornbread, an unusual customer has an unusual request. Wanting to blow off steam he wants to see about doing a fantasy where he has to escape from behind enemy lines. Chad's been hustling some of the younger kids on the range, so one of the older guys challenges him to an assault rifle challenge. Chad and Biff have to test the new sight on a 300 rifle that is being used as a hog gun, and also see an outdated Japanese Nambu.

5.title: Lords of War
5.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

6.title: Tanks for the Memories
6.plot: Steven with the help of local re-enactor Tackleberry attempt to make the dream of a father and son come true with a live fire reenactment. Kenny has to turn down his friend's gun, because they just can't see eye to on the price. Biff and Chad get to see two beautiful examples of early firearms. And Steven, despite his best efforts, can't separate work from pleasure.

7.title: Nightmare at Knob Creek
7.plot: Two customers Horror experience become a nightmare for the rest of Stevens's family while he researches what he should do. However, it all pays off in the ultimate horror movie revenge. Chad wants to do something nice for Biff and tries to round up some of the old guys to do a machine gun shoot reunion for biff. Payton convinces Kenny to get a 20 mm for the shop. And the most high-tech gun to ever walk in the door has a first time shooter on the mark in one shot.

8.title: Machine Gun Shoot
8.plot: They have to set up the assault riffle course, prep the range and figure out this year's big target. It is all hands on deck. But it the machine gun shoot wouldn't be complete with out a couple twists and turns. A couple that got engaged at last years shoot are hoping that not only can they get married during the shoot, but also they'd like Steven to be the one to perform the ceremony.

0.title: Knob Creek Range Rules and Tour
0.plot: CMT's Allison DeMarcus, takes a tour around Knob Creek Range with Owner, Biff Sumner, Jr. Next, prepare for a day of fun at the Range by getting a rundown of safety precautions from Range Safety Officer and US Military Veteran, DJ Sumner.

1.title: Son of a Gun
1.plot: As Chad and the family create an old-style "Mobster Hit" for a customer, Steven teaches Payton that shooting up other people's property comes with a big price. Meanwhile, Biff has some bad news for the owner of a seemingly rare weapon.

2.title: Cabin Fever
2.plot: Range regular Doc shows Steven & Kenny a monster M-60. Later, the Sumners stage a Civil War epic that includes the blowing-up of a cabin. Meanwhile, the range is used to settle a bet: what looks cooler blown to bits: a watermelon or a bowling ball?

3.title: New Girl
3.plot: Steven and Payton meet men who build cannons that can shoot bowling balls. Meanwhile, Gran-pa hires a new girl to work at the range - with mixed results.

4.title: Love Explosion
4.plot: Steven helps a feuding couple rekindle, first by helping them destroy their ugly furniture, and later by staging an "explosive" date out on the range. He also haggles with a seller over a rare "Book Gun."

5.title: Big Shots
5.plot: Steven and Chad convince Gran-pa Biff to let them run the range for a week. Later, the two new bosses bring in their ideas such as an artist who "paints" with guns, a wild bachelorette party complete with male strippers and a giveaway of free ammo.

6.title: A Little Bit Louder Now
6.plot: Steven, Chad and Payton create a unique home alarm system while Gran-pa Biff screens an applicant for his highly secretive "Old Timers Club," an exclusive organization that loves guns and good practical jokes.

7.title: Zombie Apocalypse
7.plot: Steven puts together a massive experience for a customer looking to take out an army of zombies. Steven also sells a replica of a very cool "Pirate" gun, the legendary Blunderbuss.

8.title: Meet the Parent
8.plot: Steven goes ballistic upon learning daughter Stephanie's new boyfriend has yet to touch a gun. Steven forces Stephanie's guy Ben into an awkward session of hunting, followed by a pro wrestling match where the overzealous dad escorts the couple.

9.title: Doomsday
9.plot: A range regular gets Steven thinking and over-thinking the scary notion of "doomsday," and he decides to get his family ready for it. A new shooter learns to fire a powerful gun into a block of ice, and over at Biff's shop, Gran-pa sells an old pistol.

10.title: Machine Gun Shoot-Out
10.plot: Biff and Nancy have a target shoot-out with Payton, teaching him the difference between U.S. rifles and German rifles used in WWII.

imdb.plot outline: Follows three generations of the Sumner family who run Knob Creek Gun Range, their family owned business in Knob Creek, Kentucky. At Knob Creek Gun Range, it's up to the Sumner family to keep things running smoothly as customers use, try out and even purchase and sell weapons across a broad spectrum of firearms, from a cannon to a machine gun. They can even blow up whatever they bring to the range.
